					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204947" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1388706077 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jan 2014 23:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1927090">
									

<p>Having looked back over the original, I know I read it, but I didn't remember it enough to apply it to this piece. As a result, I had a hell of a time following what was going on. The &quot;amnestics aren't working&quot; opening is great, it's what got me to the end, but along the way&#8230; What's going on? Who are these people? Furthermore, how many of them are there?</p>
<p>Once they start talking to the pair in the semi, the conversation became impossible to follow. I had no way of knowing who Barcode was and by the time it became clear, I'd missed everything else. (Also, the editing seems to peter out toward the end.) Also, I thought Matthew had called the semi. Also, who the fuck is Prosper? The number of characters in this seems to shift continuously.</p>
<p>You've got a great setup here, but this needs a lot of work.</p>

							</div>

								
					
